"You can encrypt your account, settings, downloaded apps and their data, media and other files. After encrypting your phone, if you have set a screen lock (pattern, numeric PIN or password), then you will need to unlock the screen to decrypt the phone every time you turn it on. Restoring to factory settings is the only other way to decrypt, but this will erase all your data.
Encryption takes at least 1 hour. Before beginning encryption, you must fully charge the battery, and keep the phone plugged in throughout the encryption process. If encryption is interrupted, some or all your data will be lost."
